Intro

Background

  • Generative Artificial Intelligence in the for form of chatbots is becoming ubiquitous in our daily lives
    • e.g.Â health care (Grote and Berens 2020), finance (DâAcunto, Prabhala, and Rossi 2019) â¦
  • The impact of AI advice on human decision-making is still largely unknown (e.g., Schemmer et al. 2022)
    • Aversion to algorithms percevied as opaque (Germann and Merkle 2022)

Research questions



What is the impact of chatbots on cooperation?


What are the consequences of a (known) bias in the chatbot?

Design

Interaction setting

Col (Other)
A B
Row (You) A 7, 7 2, 9
B 9, 2 4, 4
  • A one-shot PD
  • The participants can interact live with an AI chatbot (chatGPT)
    • Ask any question/make statements
      • In the first round they are forced to interact at least 5x

The Chatbot

Col (Other)
A B
Row (You) A 7, 7 2, 9
B 9, 2 4, 4

  • The chatbot(gpt-3.5-turbo) is either instructed to promote move A (COOP) or move B (OPPO)
    • Setting prompted by the experimenter
      • First a description of the game is provided
      • Then a set of instructions
    • Temperature set to 0.5
      • Generates conversational responses that balance coherence and diversity. see here

The Chatbot: example of a conversation

COOP

How should I play this game?
In order to maximize your earnings, I advise you to choose Option A. It has the potential to give you higher returns compared to Option B. Good luck!

If I choose A, what are my earnings?
If you choose A, your earnings depend on player âColâsâ choice. If they choose A, you both earn 7. If they choose B, you earn 2.

Why do you give me these answers?
I give you these answers to help you make strategic decisions in the game. Choosing Option A can lead to higher earnings for you.

[â¦]

OPPO

How should I play this game?
I would advise player âRowâ to choose Option B in order to maximize their earnings and potentially gain an advantage over player âColâ.

If I choose B, what are my earnings?
If you choose B, your earnings will depend on the choice of the other player. It could be either 4 or 9.

Why do you give me these answers?
I give you these answers because, based on the given conditions, choosing Option B will maximize your earnings in the game.

Treatments

Chatbot Bias

  • COOP
    • Promote Choice A
  • OPPO
    • Promote Choice B

Information Type

  • Aware
    • know that the other has access to the same algo
    • know the bias of own and otherâs algo
    • know that the other is unaware of the bias
  • Unaware
    • know that the other has access to the same algo
    • do not know the bias of own and otherâs algo

Treatments

  • T.1: Both \(A\) and \(U\) are exposed to a OPPO chatbot
  • T.2: Both \(A\) and \(U\) are exposed to a COOP chatbot

Hypotheses

Direct impact of the chatbot bias

  • H.1: \(C_U^{COOP}|B > C_U^{OPPO}|B\)
    • Given beliefs about the otherâs choice, the expected cooperation of \(U\) is higher in the COOP treatment than in the OPPO treatment, as they follow the advice of the algo and disregard their âinnateâ preferences

Hypotheses

Impact of the awareness of the bias

  • H.2: \(C_A^{COOP}|B = C_A^{COOP}|B\)

    • Given beliefs about the otherâs choice, the expected cooperation of \(A\) in COOP and in OPPO is similar, as they disregard the advice of the algo and follow their âinnateâ preferences

Implementation

Procedures and Participants

  • Preregistered on OSF
    • 2x2 between-subjects design
      • \(\sim\) 300 participants per treatment
  • Online via Prolific
    • oTree (Chen, Schonger, and Wickens 2016) + chatGPT
      • App prototype ready to deploy
  • Incentivized
    • âColdâ matching
  • No deception
  • Planned for February/March 2024

Observed Variables: Choices

  • Choice of A
    • Frequency
  • Dialogue with the bot
    • NLP analysis of the conversation
      • Sentiment
      • Complexity
      • â¦

Observed Variables: Beliefs

  • Beliefs about the partnerâs choice
    • Collected via a Binarized Scoring Rule (BSR) (Hossain and Okui 2013)
      • Incentivize truthful reporting free of risk taste assumptions
